WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.830 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.830 --> 00:00:08.150 align:middle line:84%
>> Man has made the planet and
everything on it his subject.

00:00:08.150 --> 00:00:12.500 align:middle line:84%
Livestock supply us with
meat, milk, and leather.

00:00:12.500 --> 00:00:15.650 align:middle line:84%
Around 2 million years ago, when
our ancestors were beginning

00:00:15.650 --> 00:00:18.140 align:middle line:84%
to walk upright across
the African plains,

00:00:18.140 --> 00:00:20.480 align:middle line:84%
an energy-rich food
was discovered--

00:00:20.480 --> 00:00:21.440 align:middle line:90%
meat.

00:00:21.440 --> 00:00:27.500 align:middle line:84%
>> It started with erectus
and early homo with cutting

00:00:27.500 --> 00:00:31.160 align:middle line:84%
the meat with stone
tools, grinding the meat,

00:00:31.160 --> 00:00:33.080 align:middle line:90%
pounding the meat.

00:00:33.080 --> 00:00:36.140 align:middle line:84%
>> Vegans don't eat
meat, don't drink milk,

00:00:36.140 --> 00:00:38.660 align:middle line:84%
and even deny themselves
that breakfast egg.

00:00:38.660 --> 00:00:45.022 align:middle line:90%


00:00:45.022 --> 00:00:45.980 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:00:45.980 --> 00:00:48.950 align:middle line:84%
>> For me, consuming milk and
other dairy products as animal

00:00:48.950 --> 00:00:49.970 align:middle line:90%
cruelty.

00:00:49.970 --> 00:00:52.340 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter if it's
conventional, organic,

00:00:52.340 --> 00:00:54.740 align:middle line:90%
or biodynamic milk.

00:00:54.740 --> 00:00:58.280 align:middle line:84%
>> For most city dwellers, their
only contact with livestock is

00:00:58.280 --> 00:01:01.430 align:middle line:84%
when they drink some milk or
the steak is already sizzling

00:01:01.430 --> 00:01:04.250 align:middle line:90%
in the pan, and I'm one of them.

00:01:04.250 --> 00:01:07.460 align:middle line:90%
I love cooking.

00:01:07.460 --> 00:01:12.080 align:middle line:84%
Many vegans manage without using
any animal products at all.

00:01:12.080 --> 00:01:14.900 align:middle line:84%
Does this mean they have
a healthier, better life?

00:01:14.900 --> 00:01:21.260 align:middle line:90%


00:01:21.260 --> 00:01:26.180 align:middle line:84%
In the US, the vegan wave has
long since become a tsunami.

00:01:26.180 --> 00:01:28.520 align:middle line:90%
It's a billion-dollar industry.

00:01:28.520 --> 00:01:30.860 align:middle line:84%
No wonder the first
biotech company

00:01:30.860 --> 00:01:34.130 align:middle line:84%
settled in California,
developing [INAUDIBLE]

00:01:34.130 --> 00:01:36.240 align:middle line:90%
meat and dairy products.

00:01:36.240 --> 00:01:39.260 align:middle line:84%
So is veganism really
healthier and more ethical

00:01:39.260 --> 00:01:41.780 align:middle line:84%
and environmentally friendly
than the consumption

00:01:41.780 --> 00:01:43.490 align:middle line:90%
of mass-produced meat products?

00:01:43.490 --> 00:01:58.640 align:middle line:90%


00:01:58.640 --> 00:02:01.530 align:middle line:84%
Between the Place de la
Bastille and the Place de la

00:02:01.530 --> 00:02:06.980 align:middle line:84%
Nation in Paris, the [FRENCH]
takes place six times a week.

00:02:06.980 --> 00:02:10.490 align:middle line:84%
France's culinary specialties
can all be found here.

00:02:10.490 --> 00:02:14.330 align:middle line:90%


00:02:14.330 --> 00:02:17.810 align:middle line:84%
The daily market is a temple
of the French way of life

00:02:17.810 --> 00:02:22.370 align:middle line:84%
and culture, a culinary culture
that is admired across Europe,

00:02:22.370 --> 00:02:25.940 align:middle line:90%
even across the whole world.

00:02:25.940 --> 00:02:29.270 align:middle line:84%
Deborah Pivain is a great
admirer of French cuisine.

00:02:29.270 --> 00:02:32.630 align:middle line:84%
The American has been living
in Paris for almost 40 years,

00:02:32.630 --> 00:02:35.630 align:middle line:84%
and demonstrated her
American pioneering spirit

00:02:35.630 --> 00:02:39.050 align:middle line:84%
when she opened a gourmet
vegan restaurant in Paris.

00:02:39.050 --> 00:02:41.450 align:middle line:84%
>> Actually opening a vegan
restaurant in Paris meant

00:02:41.450 --> 00:02:46.430 align:middle line:84%
mastering absolutely a vegan
cuisine and French cuisine.

00:02:46.430 --> 00:02:49.400 align:middle line:10%
And people, what they
love about French food

00:02:49.400 --> 00:02:52.070 align:middle line:10%
is the essence,
the spirit of it.

00:02:52.070 --> 00:02:55.250 align:middle line:10%
It's the technique,
very good products,

00:02:55.250 --> 00:02:59.690 align:middle line:10%
and a whole history of tastes
and textures and sensation.

00:02:59.690 --> 00:03:07.010 align:middle line:10%
So because I love the foundation
of what vegan means and I love

00:03:07.010 --> 00:03:11.300 align:middle line:10%
Paris, putting the two
together was just as perfect

00:03:11.300 --> 00:03:13.910 align:middle line:10%
as you can get.

00:03:13.910 --> 00:03:17.060 align:middle line:84%
>> As vegans use no
animal products at all,

00:03:17.060 --> 00:03:20.570 align:middle line:84%
they often make do with
plant-based dairy substitutes

00:03:20.570 --> 00:03:22.090 align:middle line:90%
in the kitchen.

00:03:22.090 --> 00:03:26.650 align:middle line:84%
Are they as easy to cook with
as our standard dairy products?

00:03:26.650 --> 00:03:28.400 align:middle line:84%
>> We have no problem
making [INAUDIBLE]..

00:03:28.400 --> 00:03:31.860 align:middle line:84%
Cakes, the macaroon,
the pate chaud,

00:03:31.860 --> 00:03:35.330 align:middle line:84%
which is used to make
eclairs, no problem.

00:03:35.330 --> 00:03:37.250 align:middle line:90%
People were ecstatic about it.

00:03:37.250 --> 00:03:39.650 align:middle line:84%
And where would we
have difficulties?

00:03:39.650 --> 00:03:46.230 align:middle line:10%
Well, cheeses are the only thing
that we are still youngsters

00:03:46.230 --> 00:03:47.030 align:middle line:10%
at.

00:03:47.030 --> 00:03:49.072 align:middle line:84%
And it's just going to
take a little bit of time,

00:03:49.072 --> 00:03:52.883 align:middle line:84%
a little bit of chemistry
to learn how to make them

00:03:52.883 --> 00:03:54.800 align:middle line:84%
with all the variety,
because the French still

00:03:54.800 --> 00:03:56.840 align:middle line:90%
have 486 varieties of cheese.

00:03:56.840 --> 00:03:58.700 align:middle line:84%
So it's taken over
a thousand years

00:03:58.700 --> 00:04:00.867 align:middle line:84%
to do that, it's going to
take us a couple of years.

00:04:00.867 --> 00:04:02.980 align:middle line:90%


00:04:02.980 --> 00:04:06.160 align:middle line:84%
>> Vegan cuisine is
unbelievably diverse.

00:04:06.160 --> 00:04:07.300 align:middle line:90%
It has to be.

00:04:07.300 --> 00:04:10.960 align:middle line:84%
All animal products are
replaced with plant-based ones.

00:04:10.960 --> 00:04:13.150 align:middle line:84%
Those who want the
flavor of a schnitzel

00:04:13.150 --> 00:04:15.490 align:middle line:90%
do not have to forgo the taste.

00:04:15.490 --> 00:04:18.040 align:middle line:84%
The secret is in the
spices and the technique

00:04:18.040 --> 00:04:21.610 align:middle line:84%
that enables you to replicate
the consistency of meat.

00:04:21.610 --> 00:04:24.492 align:middle line:84%
After all, you eat
with your eyes, too.

00:04:24.492 --> 00:04:25.450 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:04:25.450 --> 00:04:27.430 align:middle line:10%
>> Firm and tasty.

00:04:27.430 --> 00:04:32.310 align:middle line:90%


00:04:32.310 --> 00:04:33.460 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:04:33.460 --> 00:04:37.450 align:middle line:84%
>> This is pizza dough that
you put into water and kneed.

00:04:37.450 --> 00:04:39.830 align:middle line:90%
It takes up the starch.

00:04:39.830 --> 00:04:42.190 align:middle line:84%
Then you're left with
a mass that you can fry

00:04:42.190 --> 00:04:43.800 align:middle line:90%
and which tastes like pork.

00:04:43.800 --> 00:04:52.330 align:middle line:90%


00:04:52.330 --> 00:04:55.300 align:middle line:84%
Even dessert is not
something vegan chefs

00:04:55.300 --> 00:04:57.280 align:middle line:90%
have to shy away from.

00:04:57.280 --> 00:04:59.797 align:middle line:90%
It just tastes different.

00:04:59.797 --> 00:05:04.550 align:middle line:90%


00:05:04.550 --> 00:05:06.573 align:middle line:90%
White vegan chocolate.

00:05:06.573 --> 00:05:14.150 align:middle line:90%


00:05:14.150 --> 00:05:16.100 align:middle line:84%
With this skill,
there are always

00:05:16.100 --> 00:05:19.320 align:middle line:84%
new delights for the
palate to be discovered.

00:05:19.320 --> 00:05:23.180 align:middle line:84%
The vegan kitchen is in no way
behind conventional cuisine.

00:05:23.180 --> 00:05:25.680 align:middle line:90%
Either it tastes or it doesn't.

00:05:25.680 --> 00:05:28.160 align:middle line:84%
But as there is more to
eating than just nutrition,

00:05:28.160 --> 00:05:31.220 align:middle line:84%
it's worth taking a look behind
the scenes of a vegan kitchen.

00:05:31.220 --> 00:05:35.280 align:middle line:90%


00:05:35.280 --> 00:05:38.270 align:middle line:84%
The blue lupine is
a special plant.

00:05:38.270 --> 00:05:41.850 align:middle line:84%
Farmers used it as a
protein-rich pig feed.

00:05:41.850 --> 00:05:44.960 align:middle line:84%
It was very bitter, which is
why the pigs didn't like it.

00:05:44.960 --> 00:05:51.110 align:middle line:90%


00:05:51.110 --> 00:05:54.350 align:middle line:84%
The Fraunhofer Institute
for processing technology

00:05:54.350 --> 00:05:59.030 align:middle line:84%
and packaging has upgraded the
local plant to a sweet lupine

00:05:59.030 --> 00:06:01.670 align:middle line:84%
and made it suitable
for human consumption.

00:06:01.670 --> 00:06:04.180 align:middle line:90%


00:06:04.180 --> 00:06:07.700 align:middle line:84%
Lupine seeds are flaked and
undergo several processing

00:06:07.700 --> 00:06:11.780 align:middle line:84%
stages so the rich
protein can be extracted.

00:06:11.780 --> 00:06:14.960 align:middle line:84%
An established technique that
proved useful in developing

00:06:14.960 --> 00:06:18.680 align:middle line:90%
the process was decaffeination.

00:06:18.680 --> 00:06:20.420 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:06:20.420 --> 00:06:23.210 align:middle line:10%
>> To extract the protein
from sweet lupines,

00:06:23.210 --> 00:06:27.350 align:middle line:10%
they first need to be de-oiled,
similar to the soybean.

00:06:27.350 --> 00:06:29.720 align:middle line:84%
Usually various solvents
are used with soya

00:06:29.720 --> 00:06:31.460 align:middle line:90%
to remove the oil.

00:06:31.460 --> 00:06:33.950 align:middle line:84%
We wanted to find a more
environmentally-friendly

00:06:33.950 --> 00:06:38.230 align:middle line:84%
alternative and stumbled
across the overcritical CO2.

00:06:38.230 --> 00:06:40.820 align:middle line:84%
It is used for extracting
the caffeine from coffee.

00:06:40.820 --> 00:06:43.520 align:middle line:90%


00:06:43.520 --> 00:06:45.590 align:middle line:84%
With the new lupines,
we use it to remove

00:06:45.590 --> 00:06:49.250 align:middle line:84%
the oil and other aromas and
improve the plant's taste.

00:06:49.250 --> 00:06:56.240 align:middle line:90%


00:06:56.240 --> 00:06:59.630 align:middle line:84%
>> It was through cultivation,
not by means of genetic

00:06:59.630 --> 00:07:02.330 align:middle line:84%
modification, that the
scientists succeeded

00:07:02.330 --> 00:07:05.510 align:middle line:84%
in reducing the bitterness
of the sweet lupine.

00:07:05.510 --> 00:07:08.930 align:middle line:84%
This gives us a protein that
can be turned into lupine milk.

00:07:08.930 --> 00:07:11.452 align:middle line:90%


00:07:11.452 --> 00:07:12.410 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:07:12.410 --> 00:07:14.170 align:middle line:84%
>> Proteins are
nice and flaky now.

00:07:14.170 --> 00:07:21.210 align:middle line:90%


00:07:21.210 --> 00:07:24.720 align:middle line:84%
Those who want to make a
milk substitute not only

00:07:24.720 --> 00:07:28.830 align:middle line:84%
need more protein, but
also oil and sugar.

00:07:28.830 --> 00:07:31.560 align:middle line:84%
Adding water produces
a white liquid that

00:07:31.560 --> 00:07:33.150 align:middle line:90%
can be processed like milk.

00:07:33.150 --> 00:07:39.310 align:middle line:90%


00:07:39.310 --> 00:07:44.190 align:middle line:84%
Lupine milk-- competition
for any dairy farmer.

00:07:44.190 --> 00:07:47.010 align:middle line:84%
But since the milk prices
have hit rock bottom,

00:07:47.010 --> 00:07:49.650 align:middle line:84%
the farmer is grateful
for any alternatives.

00:07:49.650 --> 00:07:52.350 align:middle line:90%


00:07:52.350 --> 00:07:54.360 align:middle line:84%
More and more farmers
are considering

00:07:54.360 --> 00:07:56.400 align:middle line:90%
growing the sweet lupine.

00:07:56.400 --> 00:07:59.610 align:middle line:84%
it makes economic
sense, especially

00:07:59.610 --> 00:08:02.220 align:middle line:84%
in the sandy soil in
Northeast Germany,

00:08:02.220 --> 00:08:05.460 align:middle line:84%
the sweet lupine
is now en vogue.

00:08:05.460 --> 00:08:09.450 align:middle line:84%
As a new field crop, the lupine
takes nitrogen from the air

00:08:09.450 --> 00:08:11.265 align:middle line:90%
and passes it onto the subsoil.

00:08:11.265 --> 00:08:14.070 align:middle line:90%


00:08:14.070 --> 00:08:17.220 align:middle line:84%
For this reason,
farmer Sebastian Grewe

00:08:17.220 --> 00:08:22.630 align:middle line:84%
barely needs any pesticides
and still has a larger harvest.

00:08:22.630 --> 00:08:23.500 align:middle line:90%
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

00:08:23.500 --> 00:08:24.300 align:middle line:90%


00:08:24.300 --> 00:08:26.430 align:middle line:10%
>> Next year there will
be rye growing here,

00:08:26.430 --> 00:08:29.910 align:middle line:10%
and we can assume that we will
generate 150 euros more from

00:08:29.910 --> 00:08:31.790 align:middle line:10%
the areas where we
had lupines growing.

00:08:31.790 --> 00:08:36.309 align:middle line:90%


00:08:36.309 --> 00:08:39.450 align:middle line:84%
For farmer Grewe and his
client, Marc Zillmann,

00:08:39.450 --> 00:08:41.787 align:middle line:90%
it's a win-win situation.

00:08:41.787 --> 00:08:42.620 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING GERMAN]

00:08:42.620 --> 00:08:44.880 align:middle line:10%
>> The sweet lupine is
an indigenous plant,

00:08:44.880 --> 00:08:48.280 align:middle line:10%
so we can use protein
from the region.

00:08:48.280 --> 00:08:49.950 align:middle line:10%
It's also a great
functional plant

00:08:49.950 --> 00:08:51.450 align:middle line:10%
that can really produce milk.

00:08:51.450 --> 00:08:54.940 align:middle line:90%


00:08:54.940 --> 00:08:58.150 align:middle line:84%
Just imagine, you have
milk that's made of water,

00:08:58.150 --> 00:09:01.410 align:middle line:84%
milk fat, milk protein,
milk sugar, and all of that

00:09:01.410 --> 00:09:04.130 align:middle line:84%
needs to be reproduced if
you want a milk substitute.

00:09:04.130 --> 00:09:10.130 align:middle line:90%


00:09:10.130 --> 00:09:15.440 align:middle line:84%
The sweet lupine seeds are
easy to store and process.

00:09:15.440 --> 00:09:17.030 align:middle line:90%
This is about 30 tons.

00:09:17.030 --> 00:09:19.280 align:middle line:90%
What can you make from 30 tons?

00:09:19.280 --> 00:09:22.630 align:middle line:84%
30 tons make about
150,000 liters of milk,

00:09:22.630 --> 00:09:24.306 align:middle line:90%
so that it's quite effective.

00:09:24.306 --> 00:09:27.570 align:middle line:90%


00:09:27.570 --> 00:09:31.490 align:middle line:84%
Only a few kilometers from the
fields where the lupine grew,

00:09:31.490 --> 00:09:33.100 align:middle line:90%
the lupine milk is produced.

00:09:33.100 --> 00:09:38.760 align:middle line:90%


00:09:38.760 --> 00:09:42.420 align:middle line:84%
This is where the basis for
lupine yogurt, lupine cocoa,

00:09:42.420 --> 00:09:44.340 align:middle line:90%
and lupine ice cream is made.

00:09:44.340 --> 00:09:46.870 align:middle line:90%


00:09:46.870 --> 00:09:47.870 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:09:47.870 --> 00:09:50.230 align:middle line:84%
Lupine milk can be used
just like normal milk that

00:09:50.230 --> 00:09:51.580 align:middle line:90%
comes from a cow.

00:09:51.580 --> 00:09:54.820 align:middle line:84%
I can make my rice pudding with
it, I can eat it with my muesli

00:09:54.820 --> 00:09:56.710 align:middle line:84%
or drink it cold
out of the fridge.

00:09:56.710 --> 00:09:59.980 align:middle line:84%
There's no limits
to how I can use it.

00:09:59.980 --> 00:10:02.760 align:middle line:84%
That's the advantage, as I
don't have to give anything up.

00:10:02.760 --> 00:10:04.660 align:middle line:84%
Plant-based nutrition
is no longer

00:10:04.660 --> 00:10:07.000 align:middle line:84%
associated with sacrifice,
but with pleasure.

00:10:07.000 --> 00:10:10.410 align:middle line:90%


00:10:10.410 --> 00:10:12.990 align:middle line:84%
Although the lupine
platter is limited,

00:10:12.990 --> 00:10:16.560 align:middle line:84%
there are ecological benefits
to the local lupine not offered

00:10:16.560 --> 00:10:22.270 align:middle line:84%
by other important protein-rich
alternatives, such as soya.

00:10:22.270 --> 00:10:26.930 align:middle line:84%
35 million tons of soya are
imported by the EU each year,

00:10:26.930 --> 00:10:29.170 align:middle line:90%
mainly from South America.

00:10:29.170 --> 00:10:32.050 align:middle line:84%
Most of it is for
livestock fodder.

00:10:32.050 --> 00:10:34.840 align:middle line:84%
Large areas of rainforest
have been burnt down

00:10:34.840 --> 00:10:39.040 align:middle line:84%
to make way to farm the
monoculture, surface areas that

00:10:39.040 --> 00:10:41.470 align:middle line:90%
once soaked up CO2.

00:10:41.470 --> 00:10:44.260 align:middle line:84%
The majority of the beans have
been genetically modified,

00:10:44.260 --> 00:10:48.130 align:middle line:84%
yet the need for new
pesticides does not abate.

00:10:48.130 --> 00:10:52.000 align:middle line:84%
Soy is an important raw
material for many food products,

00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:56.380 align:middle line:84%
such as baked goods, dairy
products, and cereal bars.

00:10:56.380 --> 00:10:58.720 align:middle line:84%
To process the beans
into protein products,

00:10:58.720 --> 00:11:00.730 align:middle line:90%
they need to be de-oiled.

00:11:00.730 --> 00:11:05.020 align:middle line:84%
So far, the oil is dissolved
in the toxic chemical hexane,

00:11:05.020 --> 00:11:07.390 align:middle line:84%
which is not only harmful
for the environment,

00:11:07.390 --> 00:11:09.460 align:middle line:90%
but highly flammable.

00:11:09.460 --> 00:11:11.650 align:middle line:84%
Ecologically
sustainable it is not.

00:11:11.650 --> 00:11:16.770 align:middle line:90%


00:11:16.770 --> 00:11:20.490 align:middle line:84%
In many ways, Berlin
is setting precedents.

00:11:20.490 --> 00:11:22.470 align:middle line:84%
At the moment, the
German metropolis

00:11:22.470 --> 00:11:26.070 align:middle line:84%
is proving to be the
vegan capital of Europe.

00:11:26.070 --> 00:11:30.060 align:middle line:84%
Jan Bredack, a former manager
from the automobile industry,

00:11:30.060 --> 00:11:32.910 align:middle line:84%
is now head of a vegan
supermarket chain

00:11:32.910 --> 00:11:36.280 align:middle line:84%
and embodies this
trend like no other.

00:11:36.280 --> 00:11:38.430 align:middle line:84%
He wants to earn money
with his enterprise,

00:11:38.430 --> 00:11:42.647 align:middle line:84%
but at the same time make
the world a better place.

00:11:42.647 --> 00:11:43.480 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING GERMAN]

00:11:43.480 --> 00:11:46.950 align:middle line:84%
>> For 35 years, I myself
drank liters of milk according

00:11:46.950 --> 00:11:48.090 align:middle line:90%
to the old tradition.

00:11:48.090 --> 00:11:48.940 align:middle line:90%
It's healthy.

00:11:48.940 --> 00:11:51.990 align:middle line:84%
Because my grandmother always
said that if I ate my dairy,

00:11:51.990 --> 00:11:53.940 align:middle line:90%
I'd grow strong.

00:11:53.940 --> 00:11:58.260 align:middle line:84%
These are rituals passed down,
conditioned modes of behavior.

00:11:58.260 --> 00:12:00.660 align:middle line:84%
For me, it was the
old moment when

00:12:00.660 --> 00:12:03.180 align:middle line:84%
