Max Planck Institute

00:13:51.790 --> 00:13:54.520 align:middle line:84%
for Evolutionary
Anthropology in Leipzig

00:13:54.520 --> 00:13:56.470 align:middle line:84%
are studying the
deeper motivations

00:13:56.470 --> 00:13:59.590 align:middle line:90%
of human eating behavior.

00:13:59.590 --> 00:14:02.710 align:middle line:84%
Why do people eat meat
and other animal products?

00:14:02.710 --> 00:14:05.560 align:middle line:84%
Jean-Jacques Hublin
is finding the answers

00:14:05.560 --> 00:14:08.380 align:middle line:84%
in the prehistory
of human evolution.

00:14:08.380 --> 00:14:11.260 align:middle line:84%
The anthropologist
delves deep into the past

00:14:11.260 --> 00:14:13.315 align:middle line:84%
when apes were slowly
becoming humans.

00:14:13.315 --> 00:14:17.390 align:middle line:90%


00:14:17.390 --> 00:14:22.190 align:middle line:10%
>> Our brain is about five
times the size it should be

00:14:22.190 --> 00:14:25.370 align:middle line:10%
for a mammal our
size, our body size.

00:14:25.370 --> 00:14:27.920 align:middle line:84%
And the brain is a
very expensive tissue

00:14:27.920 --> 00:14:30.590 align:middle line:90%
in terms of energy.

00:14:30.590 --> 00:14:37.430 align:middle line:84%
It takes about 20% for what we
call basal metabolism, which

00:14:37.430 --> 00:14:41.660 align:middle line:84%
is energy we produce
at rest, and this

00:14:41.660 --> 00:14:45.770 align:middle line:84%
is consumed by an organ
that represent only 2%

00:14:45.770 --> 00:14:47.690 align:middle line:90%
of the body, so a huge cost.

00:14:47.690 --> 00:14:51.850 align:middle line:90%


00:14:51.850 --> 00:14:55.265 align:middle line:84%
>> Our early ancestors were
herbivore apes that lived

00:14:55.265 --> 00:14:56.065 align:middle line:90%
in the trees.

00:14:56.065 --> 00:14:59.230 align:middle line:90%


00:14:59.230 --> 00:15:02.110 align:middle line:84%
2 million years
ago, Homo erectus

00:15:02.110 --> 00:15:05.840 align:middle line:84%
was hunting small living
animals on the forest floor,

00:15:05.840 --> 00:15:07.630 align:middle line:90%
and brain size increased.

00:15:07.630 --> 00:15:13.570 align:middle line:90%


00:15:13.570 --> 00:15:17.680 align:middle line:84%
Our ancestor would cut the meat
from the bones with small stone

00:15:17.680 --> 00:15:19.270 align:middle line:90%
tools.

00:15:19.270 --> 00:15:23.740 align:middle line:84%
But the second spectacular phase
of the brain growth of the Homo

00:15:23.740 --> 00:15:27.520 align:middle line:84%
only happened after the
discovery of fire and cooking

00:15:27.520 --> 00:15:31.480 align:middle line:90%
over 500,000 years ago.

00:15:31.480 --> 00:15:35.800 align:middle line:84%
>> The reason why cooking is
so important is because cooking

00:15:35.800 --> 00:15:41.260 align:middle line:84%
facilitates the way we can
incorporate this high energy,

00:15:41.260 --> 00:15:46.720 align:middle line:84%
this food high and rich in
energy, especially meat.

00:15:46.720 --> 00:15:50.910 align:middle line:84%
And then we see another,
I would say, acceleration

00:15:50.910 --> 00:15:54.610 align:middle line:90%
into the brain size in hominids.

00:15:54.610 --> 00:15:56.790 align:middle line:84%
In the course of the
last 5 billion years,

00:15:56.790 --> 00:15:59.230 align:middle line:84%
there is a spectacular
increase of the brain

00:15:59.230 --> 00:16:04.410 align:middle line:84%
size without any related
increases in the body size.

00:16:04.410 --> 00:16:07.930 align:middle line:84%
So the proportion between
brain and body change again.

00:16:07.930 --> 00:16:11.470 align:middle line:90%


00:16:11.470 --> 00:16:14.590 align:middle line:84%
>> By studying the
isotopes in human bones,

00:16:14.590 --> 00:16:18.560 align:middle line:84%
the scientists can ascertain
what humans were eating 500,000

00:16:18.560 --> 00:16:19.360 align:middle line:90%
years ago.

00:16:19.360 --> 00:16:21.950 align:middle line:90%


00:16:21.950 --> 00:16:24.440 align:middle line:90%
And it becomes evident.

00:16:24.440 --> 00:16:26.780 align:middle line:10%
From an evolutionary
perspective,

00:16:26.780 --> 00:16:30.050 align:middle line:10%
our metabolism is
still in the Stone Age.

00:16:30.050 --> 00:16:34.220 align:middle line:84%
We are good at storing
fat for bad times.

00:16:34.220 --> 00:16:37.310 align:middle line:84%
But as we no longer have to
hunt for the food ourselves,

00:16:37.310 --> 00:16:43.160 align:middle line:84%
but more often than not sit
lazily on the sofa, we get ill.

00:16:43.160 --> 00:16:46.970 align:middle line:84%
Our extremely high energy diet
combined with little movement

00:16:46.970 --> 00:16:52.410 align:middle line:84%
causes civilization diseases
such as cancer or diabetes.

00:16:52.410 --> 00:16:55.430 align:middle line:84%
>> But modern societies
are face a new challenge,

00:16:55.430 --> 00:17:01.370 align:middle line:84%
