Can a purely vegan diet be
dangerous or even lethal?

00:23:44.150 --> 00:23:47.510 align:middle line:10%
Why did these
children have to die?

00:23:47.510 --> 00:23:50.900 align:middle line:10%
In Germany, scientists
are seeking answers

00:23:50.900 --> 00:23:52.160 align:middle line:10%
to these questions.

00:23:52.160 --> 00:23:55.430 align:middle line:90%


00:23:55.430 --> 00:23:58.910 align:middle line:84%
Professor Bernhard Watzl
is head of the Max Rubener

00:23:58.910 --> 00:24:03.397 align:middle line:84%
Institute for Physiology and
Biochemistry of Nutrition.

00:24:03.397 --> 00:24:04.230 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING GERMAN]

00:24:04.230 --> 00:24:08.150 align:middle line:10%
>> Infants, small children
are growing organisms.

00:24:08.150 --> 00:24:10.730 align:middle line:10%
Compared to adults,
it's very important

00:24:10.730 --> 00:24:15.630 align:middle line:10%
that all necessary nutrients are
amply supplied in their diet.

00:24:15.630 --> 00:24:18.110 align:middle line:84%
The need is especially
high in small children,

00:24:18.110 --> 00:24:21.560 align:middle line:84%
and an important
example is vitamin B12.

00:24:21.560 --> 00:24:25.700 align:middle line:84%
Vitamin B12 is found in
meat, fish, eggs, and milk.

00:24:25.700 --> 00:24:29.000 align:middle line:84%
A B12 deficiency causes
tiredness, weakness,

00:24:29.000 --> 00:24:32.360 align:middle line:84%
and depression, and can
lead to irreparable damage

00:24:32.360 --> 00:24:34.370 align:middle line:90%
in the central nervous system.

00:24:34.370 --> 00:24:38.410 align:middle line:84%
Many dairy substitutes
contain artificial B12.

00:24:38.410 --> 00:24:42.950 align:middle line:84%
A chemical analysis shows a high
level of industrial processing

00:24:42.950 --> 00:24:44.870 align:middle line:90%
in these substitute foods.

00:24:44.870 --> 00:24:47.690 align:middle line:10%
They are an artificial
mix of substances

00:24:47.690 --> 00:24:50.720 align:middle line:10%
that try to emulate the
original, a mix that's

00:24:50.720 --> 00:24:53.290 align:middle line:10%
not necessarily healthier.

00:24:53.290 --> 00:24:54.890 align:middle line:10%
>> [SPEAKING GERMAN]

00:24:54.890 --> 00:24:57.740 align:middle line:10%
>> There's no scientific study
that shows it's healthier

00:24:57.740 --> 00:25:01.190 align:middle line:10%
to not drink milk, and
ultimately one food product

00:25:01.190 --> 00:25:04.310 align:middle line:10%
won't determine whether
your diet is healthy or not.

00:25:04.310 --> 00:25:06.410 align:middle line:90%
Diversity is important.

00:25:06.410 --> 00:25:11.390 align:middle line:84%
I need the vegetable part,
I need the meat part.

00:25:11.390 --> 00:25:14.000 align:middle line:84%
I can have a healthy diet
without the animal parts,

00:25:14.000 --> 00:25:16.520 align:middle line:84%
but then I'm in a situation
where I need supplements.

00:25:16.520 --> 00:25:19.190 align:middle line:90%


00:25:19.190 --> 00:25:21.650 align:middle line:84%
That's necessary if you
want to have a diet that's

00:25:21.650 --> 00:25:22.970 align:middle line:90%
entirely plant-based.

00:25:22.970 --> 00:25:27.290 align:middle line:90%


00:25:27.290 --> 00:25:30.620 align:middle line:84%
Nature really did intend for
us to have a mixed diet, not

00:25:30.620 --> 00:25:33.680 align:middle line:84%
to the extent that we are
eating animal products today--

00:25:33.680 --> 00:25:36.740 align:middle line:84%
we obviously have too much,
but some meat in our diet

00:25:36.740 --> 00:25:38.810 align:middle line:84%
is an essential
foundation if you want

00:25:38.810 --> 00:25:40.560 align:middle line:90%
to eat without supplements.

00:25:40.560 --> 00:25:45.520 align:middle line:90%


00:25:45.520 --> 00:25:48.460 align:middle line:84%
So vegans are healthy when
they use a toothpaste that

00:25:48.460 --> 00:25:50.200 align:middle line:90%
contains B12, for example.

00:25:50.200 --> 00:25:52.840 align:middle line:90%


00:25:52.840 --> 00:25:55.380 align:middle line:84%
Or they take vitamin
tablets every day.

00:25:55.380 --> 00:25:59.260 align:middle line:84%
For many, it's a better
alternative to consuming milk.

00:25:59.260 --> 00:26:01.900 align:middle line:90%


00:26:01.900 --> 00:26:03.950 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING GERMAN]

00:26:03.950 --> 00:26:07.340 align:middle line:84%
>> Alternatives that readily
replace the function of milk

00:26:07.340 --> 00:26:09.410 align:middle line:84%
are usually less
beneficial in their makeup.

00:26:09.410 --> 00:26:13.250 align:middle line:90%


00:26:13.250 --> 00:26:15.500 align:middle line:84%
They don't have the
same concentration

00:26:15.500 --> 00:26:20.540 align:middle line:84%
of the vital nutrients, are
often technologically produced,

00:26:20.540 --> 00:26:23.450 align:middle line:84%
and less beneficial to
one's health in comparison

00:26:23.450 --> 00:26:24.710 align:middle line:90%
to the makeup of milk.

00:26:24.710 --> 00:26:31.070 align:middle line:90%


00:26:31.070 --> 00:26:34.370 align:middle line:84%
Highly processed food does
not have the reputation

00:26:34.370 --> 00:26:36.200 align:middle line:90%
of being healthy.

00:26:36.200 --> 00:26:40.060 align:middle line:84%
Daniela Krehl, consumer
protectionist, explains.

00:26:40.060 --> 00:26:41.300 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:26:41.300 --> 00:26:45.030 align:middle line:84%
>> Soya was the first
milk substitute.

00:26:45.030 --> 00:26:48.592 align:middle line:84%
Now a wealth of other
substitutes have been found.

00:26:48.592 --> 00:26:49.550 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:26:49.550 --> 00:26:52.520 align:middle line:84%
>> And have you
looked what's in them?

00:26:52.520 --> 00:26:53.600 align:middle line:10%
>> Yes.

00:26:53.600 --> 00:26:57.590 align:middle line:10%
One tries to imitate milk
by adding flavorings,

00:26:57.590 --> 00:27:01.250 align:middle line:10%
but also certain vitamins
that are in milk, whether it's

00:27:01.250 --> 00:27:04.310 align:middle line:10%
calcium or B12.

00:27:04.310 --> 00:27:06.860 align:middle line:84%
These are vitamins
that are vital when

00:27:06.860 --> 00:27:10.010 align:middle line:90%
one is on a vegan diet.

00:27:10.010 --> 00:27:13.190 align:middle line:84%
And there is, of course,
sugar to give it more flavor.

00:27:13.190 --> 00:27:16.670 align:middle line:84%
Around a cube of sugar
for every 100 milliliters.

00:27:16.670 --> 00:27:20.930 align:middle line:84%
These recipes are trying to
emulate milk and its nutrients.

00:27:20.930 --> 00:27:26.980 align:middle line:90%


00:27:26.980 --> 00:27:30.220 align:middle line:84%
>> These chemical
recipes are expensive,

00:27:30.220 --> 00:27:33.260 align:middle line:84%
and there are still problems
with the taste of substitute

00:27:33.260 --> 00:27:34.060 align:middle line:90%
cheese.

00:27:34.060 --> 00:27:37.000 align:middle line:90%


00:27:37.000 --> 00:27:38.390 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:27:38.390 --> 00:27:40.650 align:middle line:90%
>> Many vegans miss cheese.

00:27:40.650 --> 00:27:43.610 align:middle line:84%
The base ingredient
is a type of oil.

00:27:43.610 --> 00:27:47.420 align:middle line:84%
So you need plant oil so it
looks like cheese and tastes

00:27:47.420 --> 00:27:51.100 align:middle line:84%
like cheese, and you can't
do that without additives.

00:27:51.100 --> 00:27:54.160 align:middle line:90%
>> And what are the additives?

00:27:54.160 --> 00:27:58.790 align:middle line:84%
>> First you need a thickener
so the oil becomes a solid mass,

00:27:58.790 --> 00:28:03.380 align:middle line:84%
and then natural coloring so it
has a nice yellow cheese color.

00:28:03.380 --> 00:28:06.980 align:middle line:84%
More important is that you
can't do it without flavorings,

00:28:06.980 --> 00:28:09.530 align:middle line:84%
as plant oil doesn't
taste like cheese,

00:28:09.530 --> 00:28:11.570 align:middle line:84%
which is the taste
we're trying to imitate.

00:28:11.570 --> 00:28:14.230 align:middle line:90%


00:28:14.230 --> 00:28:17.590 align:middle line:10%
>> As vegan cheese isn't
cheese and milk substitutes

00:28:17.590 --> 00:28:20.830 align:middle line:10%
aren't animal products, they
cannot be labeled as milk

00:28:20.830 --> 00:28:24.110 align:middle line:10%
or cheese in Europe.

00:28:24.110 --> 00:28:26.350 align:middle line:84%
Alexander Anton
makes sure of it.

00:28:26.350 --> 00:28:28.980 align:middle line:84%
He's a lobbyist for the
European milk industry.

00:28:28.980 --> 00:28:32.472 align:middle line:90%


00:28:32.472 --> 00:28:33.430 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:28:33.430 --> 00:28:35.340 align:middle line:90%
>> Pleasure, flavor, health.

00:28:35.340 --> 00:28:37.160 align:middle line:10%
This is the trial of milk.

00:28:37.160 --> 00:28:40.460 align:middle line:10%
Milk is unique in its
nutritional makeup, a product

00:28:40.460 --> 00:28:44.340 align:middle line:10%
that is traditional, that we've
been farming for 10,000 years,

00:28:44.340 --> 00:28:47.840 align:middle line:10%
and that has a natural basis.

00:28:47.840 --> 00:28:50.720 align:middle line:84%
All 1,200 French
cheese varieties

00:28:50.720 --> 00:28:54.390 align:middle line:84%
are made from the
natural food milk.

00:28:54.390 --> 00:28:57.410 align:middle line:10%
Whether soy, oat,
or almond milk,

00:28:57.410 --> 00:28:59.810 align:middle line:10%
there are concrete
economic interests

00:28:59.810 --> 00:29:02.650 align:middle line:10%
which have led to a
true labeling war.

00:29:02.650 --> 00:29:06.260 align:middle line:84%
The description milk is only
allowed with coconut milk

00:29:06.260 --> 00:29:08.276 align:middle line:90%
for traditional reasons.

00:29:08.276 --> 00:29:09.250 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:29:09.250 --> 00:29:11.180 align:middle line:84%
>> There's no real
disagreement on this.

00:29:11.180 --> 00:29:12.820 align:middle line:90%
The situation is clear.

00:29:12.820 --> 00:29:16.670 align:middle line:84%
The description of milk and milk
products is consumer-protected.

00:29:16.670 --> 00:29:18.530 align:middle line:84%
As a consumer, I
have to be informed

00:29:18.530 --> 00:29:20.780 align:middle line:84%
that when I buy cheese,
butter, or milk,

00:29:20.780 --> 00:29:23.510 align:middle line:84%
that these are real
dairy products.

00:29:23.510 --> 00:29:27.380 align:middle line:84%
Jan Bredack considers the
argument as superfluous and not

00:29:27.380 --> 00:29:29.300 align:middle line:84%
in the interests
of the consumer.

00:29:29.300 --> 00:29:32.090 align:middle line:84%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH] >>
We're not allowed to write

00:29:32.090 --> 00:29:34.460 align:middle line:84%
on our products that
they're cholesterol-free,

00:29:34.460 --> 00:29:36.050 align:middle line:90%
although they are.

00:29:36.050 --> 00:29:38.090 align:middle line:10%
That would be a
competitive disadvantage

00:29:38.090 --> 00:29:41.330 align:middle line:10%
for the meat and dairy industry
as their products contain

00:29:41.330 --> 00:29:42.740 align:middle line:10%
cholesterol.

00:29:42.740 --> 00:29:45.500 align:middle line:10%
The second issue relevant
for me here in Germany

00:29:45.500 --> 00:29:47.030 align:middle line:10%
is the tax disadvantages.

00:29:47.030 --> 00:29:50.690 align:middle line:90%


00:29:50.690 --> 00:29:54.890 align:middle line:84%
For a milk substitute,
you pay 19% VAT.

00:29:54.890 --> 00:29:59.730 align:middle line:84%
For milk from a sheep,
goat, or cow, you pay 7%.

00:29:59.730 --> 00:30:02.570 align:middle line:84%
These are things that have been
secured where the lobbyists

00:30:02.570 --> 00:30:04.070 align:middle line:90%
have done their work well.

00:30:04.070 --> 00:30:06.710 align:middle line:90%


00:30:06.710 --> 00:30:09.230 align:middle line:10%
Consumer issues like
these are negotiated

00:30:09.230 --> 00:30:12.740 align:middle line:10%
in the corridors of the EU
in Brussels and in court.

00:30:12.740 --> 00:30:14.700 align:middle line:90%
It is a billion-dollar industry.

00:30:14.700 --> 00:30:17.180 align:middle line:84%
The already shaken
milk farmers in Europe

00:30:17.180 --> 00:30:20.622 align:middle line:84%
are fighting for the image
of milk as a quality product.

00:30:20.622 --> 00:30:21.580 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:30:21.580 --> 00:30:24.680 align:middle line:84%
>> Misdescribing products that
rely on a good reputation,

00:30:24.680 --> 00:30:27.990 align:middle line:84%
that have acquired the good
image of milk is not new.

00:30:27.990 --> 00:30:30.590 align:middle line:84%
We've known this since
the era of Napoleon III.

00:30:30.590 --> 00:30:33.390 align:middle line:84%
For him, good butter was too
expensive for his troops,

00:30:33.390 --> 00:30:34.810 align:middle line:90%
so margarine was invented.

00:30:34.810 --> 00:30:39.920 align:middle line:90%


00:30:39.920 --> 00:30:42.410 align:middle line:10%
Since Napoleon III,
cheap margarine

00:30:42.410 --> 00:30:44.990 align:middle line:10%
has conquered its
place in many kitchens,

00:30:44.990 --> 00:30:49.340 align:middle line:10%
and history seems to
be repeating itself.

00:30:49.340 --> 00:30:51.890 align:middle line:84%
This Ruegenwalder
Muehle is a symbol

00:30:51.890 --> 00:30:55.490 align:middle line:84%
for the traditional meat and
sausage industry in Germany.

00:30:55.490 --> 00:30:58.490 align:middle line:84%
The business has been
undergoing radical change

00:30:58.490 --> 00:31:02.180 align:middle line:84%
since its marketing and
development head, Godo Roben,

00:31:02.180 --> 00:31:04.820 align:middle line:84%
added vegetarian
and soon vegan meats

00:31:04.820 --> 00:31:07.252 align:middle line:90%
to the company's repertoire.

00:31:07.252 --> 00:31:09.110 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:31:09.110 --> 00:31:12.213 align:middle line:84%
>> We've been producing
meats for 182 years.

00:31:12.213 --> 00:31:13.880 align:middle line:10%
And when I came up
with the idea that we

00:31:13.880 --> 00:31:17.590 align:middle line:10%
should make vegetarian products,
there were murmurs of why?

00:31:17.590 --> 00:31:20.400 align:middle line:10%
But the numbers
justified so easily.

00:31:20.400 --> 00:31:23.300 align:middle line:10%
It's not the 7 million
vegetarians the 1 million

00:31:23.300 --> 00:31:27.380 align:middle line:10%
vegans, but the 14 million
flexitarians that are saying,

00:31:27.380 --> 00:31:30.650 align:middle line:10%
I want to consume
less meat and sausage.

00:31:30.650 --> 00:31:32.180 align:middle line:84%
A serious argument
is you don't want

00:31:32.180 --> 00:31:34.558 align:middle line:84%
to lose, to the cheese
and Nutella industry,

00:31:34.558 --> 00:31:36.600 align:middle line:84%
but you want to offer them
contemporary products.

00:31:36.600 --> 00:31:41.240 align:middle line:90%


00:31:41.240 --> 00:31:45.560 align:middle line:84%
An appointment at the
Ruegenwalder base.

00:31:45.560 --> 00:31:50.570 align:middle line:84%
A challenge for vegan
blogger Anna-Lena Klapp.

00:31:50.570 --> 00:31:52.280 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:31:52.280 --> 00:31:55.280 align:middle line:10%
>> I would like to see how
seriously they take this.

00:31:55.280 --> 00:31:56.810 align:middle line:10%
How do they even do it?

00:31:56.810 --> 00:31:59.750 align:middle line:10%
How is the production of
these foods different?

00:31:59.750 --> 00:32:02.090 align:middle line:90%
And yes, what is the motivation?

00:32:02.090 --> 00:32:07.820 align:middle line:90%


00:32:07.820 --> 00:32:12.290 align:middle line:84%
>> Every week, the company
processes around 450 tons

00:32:12.290 --> 00:32:13.340 align:middle line:90%
of pork and poultry.

00:32:13.340 --> 00:32:16.940 align:middle line:90%


00:32:16.940 --> 00:32:20.760 align:middle line:84%
Pate and ham are ever
the favorite classics.

00:32:20.760 --> 00:32:24.455 align:middle line:84%
Anna-Lena finds it hard to
even look at these products.

00:32:24.455 --> 00:32:34.500 align:middle line:90%


00:32:34.500 --> 00:32:39.240 align:middle line:84%
But the enterprise already
has 11 meatless variations

00:32:39.240 --> 00:32:43.050 align:middle line:84%
in its repertoire, two
of which are vegan.

00:32:43.050 --> 00:32:46.020 align:middle line:84%
It took three years for the
first vegetarian sausage

00:32:46.020 --> 00:32:47.790 align:middle line:90%
to be brought to the market.

00:32:47.790 --> 00:32:51.060 align:middle line:84%
For Anna-Lena, the change
can't come fast enough.

00:32:51.060 --> 00:32:53.192 align:middle line:90%


00:32:53.192 --> 00:32:54.150 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:32:54.150 --> 00:32:57.360 align:middle line:84%
>> This is where the animals
that you want to free are still

00:32:57.360 --> 00:32:58.530 align:middle line:90%
processed.

00:32:58.530 --> 00:33:00.330 align:middle line:84%
It is a funny
feeling, but I think

00:33:00.330 --> 00:33:03.040 align:middle line:84%
it is moving in the
right direction.

00:33:03.040 --> 00:33:05.700 align:middle line:84%
And I hope that in the
future, animal products

00:33:05.700 --> 00:33:08.550 align:middle line:90%
will decrease a lot.

00:33:08.550 --> 00:33:10.920 align:middle line:84%
And that one day this
venture will only produce

00:33:10.920 --> 00:33:12.675 align:middle line:90%
vegetarian or vegan products.

00:33:12.675 --> 00:33:15.850 align:middle line:90%


00:33:15.850 --> 00:33:18.960 align:middle line:84%
>> However, the resistance
against vegetarian and vegan

00:33:18.960 --> 00:33:22.440 align:middle line:84%
products was considerable,
even within the company.

00:33:22.440 --> 00:33:26.020 align:middle line:84%
Yet, success was on
Godo Roben's side.

00:33:26.020 --> 00:33:28.350 align:middle line:84%
The company has had
to hire more staff

00:33:28.350 --> 00:33:31.352 align:middle line:84%
to produce the non-meat
products in three shifts.

00:33:31.352 --> 00:33:32.310 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:33:32.310 --> 00:33:34.410 align:middle line:84%
>> We haven't had much
growth in recent years.

00:33:34.410 --> 00:33:37.230 align:middle line:84%
We would have had
about 1%, 2% plus.

00:33:37.230 --> 00:33:39.480 align:middle line:84%
Now that we've introduced
vegetarian products,

00:33:39.480 --> 00:33:41.340 align:middle line:90%
our growth is in double figures.

00:33:41.340 --> 00:33:43.410 align:middle line:84%
We make about 50
million euros a year

00:33:43.410 --> 00:33:45.240 align:middle line:90%
with our vegetarian products.

00:33:45.240 --> 00:33:47.608 align:middle line:90%
That's 20% of our total revenue.

00:33:47.608 --> 00:33:49.650 align:middle line:84%
So there's really something
happening in Germany,

00:33:49.650 --> 00:33:53.010 align:middle line:90%
it's not about to stop.

00:33:53.010 --> 00:33:55.770 align:middle line:84%
Aside from the vegetarian
offer, the company

00:33:55.770 --> 00:33:58.140 align:middle line:90%
is increasing its vegan platter.

00:33:58.140 --> 00:34:01.250 align:middle line:90%
Vegan makes business sense.

00:34:01.250 --> 00:34:04.590 align:middle line:84%
Veganz founder, Bredack, wants
to conquer the European market

00:34:04.590 --> 00:34:06.510 align:middle line:90%
with his vegan supermarkets.

00:34:06.510 --> 00:34:09.569 align:middle line:84%
France is right at
the top of the list.

00:34:09.569 --> 00:34:10.500 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:34:10.500 --> 00:34:12.179 align:middle line:84%
>> We're in talks
with Carrefour.

00:34:12.179 --> 00:34:14.520 align:middle line:84%
It's not that far-fetched,
the interest is there.

00:34:14.520 --> 00:34:16.710 align:middle line:10%
But there's more from
Carrefour in Spain,

00:34:16.710 --> 00:34:20.969 align:middle line:10%
but that has an
effect on France.

00:34:20.969 --> 00:34:22.290 align:middle line:10%
I say it's France's turn.

00:34:22.290 --> 00:34:28.090 align:middle line:90%


00:34:28.090 --> 00:34:31.760 align:middle line:84%
In Berlin, this vegan
future has already begun.

00:34:31.760 --> 00:34:35.260 align:middle line:84%
Whether lupines or soy milk,
plant-based cheese or meat

00:34:35.260 --> 00:34:38.110 align:middle line:84%
substitute, the array
of products is growing

00:34:38.110 --> 00:34:40.030 align:middle line:90%
and sales are booming.

00:34:40.030 --> 00:34:44.310 align:middle line:84%
Many others are jumping
aboard the trend.

00:34:44.310 --> 00:34:45.179 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:34:45.179 --> 00:34:48.239 align:middle line:84%
>> Veganism is a trend,
